overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application to verify adherence to the provided Statement of Work and detailed
  specifications. The agent conducted a thorough analysis, identifying several
  critical gaps and missing features across various aspects of the application.
  Subsequently, the agent systematically implemented all high and medium
  priority items. This included adding a 1-10 tiredness severity scale with
  safety messaging, implementing detection and recommendations for COMISA and
  Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, integrating placeholder outbound links to
  relevant external resources, and introducing a weighted scoring system for
  Excessive Daytime Sleepiness. Furthermore, the CSV export functionality was
  enhanced to include all questionnaire data, and new questions for pain
  severity, chronic fatigue screening, and medical/mental health history were
  added to the questionnaire and reflected in the reports. The agent ensured all
  necessary code changes were applied across types, validations, UI components,
  API routes, and PDF generation.
